[
    {
        "content": "<p>I know for <code>@[to_additive ]</code>, it can be maked using @[to_additive xxx \"xxx\" ]. But in the <code>mk_iff</code> case, it's no longer works.  Is there any good way to solve this?</p>",
        "id": 513117607,
        "sender_full_name": "张守信(Shouxin Zhang)",
        "timestamp": 1745025442
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If everything else fails,</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/--</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">foo bar</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"n\">add_decl_doc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">other_declaration</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>should work iirc.</p>",
        "id": 513147847,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1745050395
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">mk_iff</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">what</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">99</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/--</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">`Example a` is true exactly when `a` is 3 or 99</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"n\">add_decl_doc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">example_iff</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 513148160,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1745050651
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"873547\">Robin Arnez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/How.20to.20make.20a.20docstring.20for.20.40.5Bmk_iff.5D.3F/near/513147847\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If everything else fails,</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/--</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">foo bar</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"n\">add_decl_doc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">other_declaration</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>should work iirc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Great! It works well. Thank you!</p>",
